<TITLE> PM greets triumphant Tigers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 22 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has said she intends to reward members of the Bangladesh cricket team with a gift of Tk 300,000 each for their recent decisive victories over the West Indies and Zimbabwe. "You have glorified the image of Bangladesh. The whole nation is ecstatic over the wins and I am convinced you will continue with your winning streak," Hasina told the recently returned players at a reception at her official residence Jamuna on Saturday. Captain Saqib Al Hasan presented a cricket bat signed by the victorious Bangladesh cricket team to the prime minister, who said the squad would be thrown a lavish reception at the end of August, when the national month of mourning ended. Hasina said her government planned to develop sport in the country, and it recognised the importance of having sufficient open areas to in the city for sporting activities. "From now on some playgrounds will be maintained in areas where high rise buildings would have been built," she said. The Bangladesh cricket team defeated the West Indies 2-0 in their first test series, and 3-0 in the one-day series. The team also notched up a record defeat of Zimbabwe, winning 4-1 in the one-day series. Bangladesh also savoured victory in 1997, when they became ICC champions, and defeated former world champions Pakistan in the 1999 World Cup. The players, coach and manager of the national cricket team were present at the occasion. Foreign minister Dipu Moni, state minister for sport Ahad Ali Sarkar and Bangladesh Cricket Board president Sina Ibne Jamali also attended the event. bdn
